modName: Armed to the Teeth - Custom Weapons
summary: This compilation adds a number of custom weapons to the Armed to the Teeth mod by Mergweq, EwokJedi and Dahaka002011. Prepare to look like a true dovahkiin with your favorite weapons.
descriptionHtml:
[color=#ff0000][size=4][b]This patch collection is no longer supported. Please see the sticky in the comments!
[/b][/size][/color][color=#ff0000][size=4][b]Better alternatives to ATTT:[/b][/size][/color] [size=4][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/49784]Equipping Overhaul[/url], [/size][size=4][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/40953/?]All Geared Up[/url],Â [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/34155]Dual Sheath Redux[/url], and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/3903]Visible Favorited Gear (SSE)[/url][/size]

You need to have the latest version of Armed to the Teeth installed for this to work properly.
You can get that here: [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=9614]Armed to the Teeth[/url]

[b][center][color=#71A1D4]Latest Update[/color][/center][/b]
[b][center][color=#77c54c]May 21st[/color][/center][/b]
[b][center][color=#71A1D4]Version 3[/color][/center][/b]


Armed to the Teeth is a scripting base that enables users to make their character look like the true bad-ass hero that the legends say they should be.

Fellow gamer Necroscope86 has graciously featured Armed to the Teeth in his video Let's Update Skyrim preceding the upcoming episode to his Let's Play series, featuring a heavily modded Skyrim. So huge thanks to him and be sure to check out his other videos!
[youtube]FKMKUwGPqNY[/youtube]


"In vanilla skyrim a character that uses a sword, 2h axe, and bow can only see the weapon that is currently equipped, the rest are just hidden magically in the inventory. This mod allows the other weapons to be seen in their sheathed positions while another weapon is active. Example: When using a sword, both my bow and 2h axe appear sheathed on my back. I can switch to my bow and my sword will then become sheathed at the hip. Staves and Shield-on-Back are also both fully working."


Now with this add-on pack, you may experience this awesome mod with your favorite custom weapon mods and strike fear into your enemies. I will take requests and complete more weapon sets as time goes on, should I get proper permissions.


Keep in mind, this is a set of PATCHES. Meaning you MUST have downloaded the respective mod (and version) of choice in order for this to work.

[color=#d04431][b]Important Note![/b] Make sure to check your mod version against the patch version! If they are not the same you WILL have issues.[/color]

V3 -- May 21st

- Added 25 new weapon and shield mods. See master list below for details.
- Added 6 new weapon mods from misiek023. See master list below for details.
- Merged with misiek023's pack
- Added AttT converted shields to Multi-Glass
- Added/Updated Weapons of the Third Era [MoS Edition] to Version 1.41
- Removed Weapons of the Third Era [Fixed]
- Updated DCR Blade Set to Version 1.1D
- Updated Dragonbone Weapons to Version 3.1.6
- Updated Legend of Zelda Biggoron to Version 2.0
- Updated LOTR Weapons Collection to Version 3.0
- Updated Ripper Sword to Version 1.1
- Updated Sai to Version 1.3
- Updated The Loners Sword to Version 1.1
- Replaced JaySuS Swords 13C with Version 13D
- Fixed script for Lord Armor

V2 -- April 26th

- Added a separate patch for JaySuS Swords 13D

V2 -- April 25th

- Added 25 new weapon/shield mods
- Added properly adjusted meshes for staves and playable instruments
- Fixed LOTR Shield placements

V1 -- April 17th

- Released with 9 included mods
